reviewText: The primary question a prospective buyer has is in regard to the quality of the DVD and subtitles; in this case, both are satisfactory.  I had been looking for a copy for several years and was happy to find this one.  Although it is more difficult to watch than any of Kim Rae Won's other work (because I hate to see him get beaten up), he created a character completely different than any other I have seen, which really shows his versatility.
